cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.SY

The paper discusses cache attacks on ARM-based mobile devices, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The attacks also involve covert channels and monitoring user input, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and system software (cs.SE). Additionally, the attacks can potentially affect the security of the ARM TrustZone, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
